  },
  {
    question: 'Which treading water technique is the least exhausting?',
    answer: 'The eggbeater kick is widely considered the most efficient and least tiring treading water technique. It is the standard method used by water polo players and lifeguards. While it takes slightly more practice to coordinate compared to a breaststroke kick, it provides continuous lift with minimal energy expenditure.'
  },
