    question: 'Why do I sink when trying to tread water?',
    answer: 'The most common reasons are: (1) Muscle tension - tensing your neck and shoulders makes your body denser and causes you to sink; (2) Kicking vertically - pushing your legs straight down and pulling them back up creates downward drag; (3) Breathing issues - exhaling completely reduces your lungs\' natural buoyancy.'
  },
  {
    question: 'At what age can children learn to tread water?',
    answer: 'Children aged 5-6 and above, who can understand and follow instructions, are fully capable of learning survival treading skills. In Swim For Life\'s kids classes, we teach treading water through interactive games to keep it engaging and safe.'
